Olive Oil
1 capsicum
½ tin sweetcorn
½ lemon
1 block haloumi/grill cheese
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 packet BBQ Mayo
1 bunch coriander

Slice capsicum into strips.
Drain sweetcorn (1/2 tin for 2P / 1 tin for 4P).
Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat.
Cook capsicum and corn, tossing, until softened and charred, 3-4 mins.
Transfer to a bowl.

Meanwhile, cut lemon into wedges. Pat haloumi dry and cut into 8, even slices.
In a bowl, combine spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Add haloumi and toss to coat.
Return frying pan to medium-high heat with olive oil.
Cook haloumi until golden brown, 1-2 mins each side.

Now, microwave tortillas for 10 second bursts, until warmed through.
Add slaw, BBQ mayo and a good squeeze of lemon juice to the veggies. Season and toss.
Fill tortillas with veggie slaw and haloumi. Tear over coriander.
Serve with remaining lemon wedges.